==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Helpmate
<hw>Help"mate`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A corruption of
the ⟦ldquo⟧<ets>help meet</ets> for him⟦rdquo⟧ of <au>Genesis ii.
18.</au><au>Fitzedward Hall.</au>]</ety> <def>A helper; a companion;
specifically, a wife.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In Minorca the ass and the hog are common <qex>helpmates</qex>,
and are yoked together in order to turn up the land.</q>
<rj><qau>Pennant.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A waiting woman was generally considered as the most suitable
<qex>helpmate</qex> for a parson.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Helpmeet</ent>⟦br⟧
